WEBVTT

01:36.406 --> 01:37.656
"Thalapathy"

01:41.198 --> 01:42.323
"Thalapathy"

01:44.156 --> 01:45.281
"His entry spells power"

01:45.323 --> 01:47.239
"Who is our master?
Commander...!"

02:11.534 --> 02:13.075
Mother

02:16.867 --> 02:18.242
'Appa...!'

02:28.659 --> 02:30.200
'Let's kill this boy also, partner'

02:30.242 --> 02:33.242
If we burn all the evidence
we will be the prime suspects

02:33.284 --> 02:35.617
'We need a witness
to speak in our favor'

02:35.659 --> 02:37.034
All that is fine

02:37.075 --> 02:40.784
Just like his father, what if he also
makes trouble insisting on being truthful?

02:41.075 --> 02:42.575
Let's find out right away

02:42.909 --> 02:44.825
Hey boy
What's your name?

02:45.354 --> 02:46.937
- Bhavani
- Huh?

02:47.909 --> 02:48.825
Bhavani

02:48.867 --> 02:50.492
How did your parents die?

02:53.450 --> 02:55.492
They were burnt to death
in a gas explosion

02:55.534 --> 02:57.159
[loud laughter]

02:59.534 --> 03:01.117
He sure knows to survive, I say

03:01.200 --> 03:02.909
After we use him as a witness

03:02.950 --> 03:05.659
...let us complain against him
for stealing our union funds

03:05.700 --> 03:07.284
'His father is Lorry Union leader'

03:07.325 --> 03:10.034
If we claim his son stole union cash
will anyone believe that story?

03:10.075 --> 03:11.992
Sudden show of mercy, huh?

03:12.075 --> 03:13.992
He's so young, that's why

03:14.034 --> 03:15.992
Hey boy, listen

03:16.950 --> 03:19.784
I'll send you to a place where boys
like you are well looked after

03:19.825 --> 03:21.617
Will you go there?

03:23.867 --> 03:26.909
'Govt Juvenile Observation Home
Nagercoil, Kallakurichi'

03:28.825 --> 03:31.950
'That boy shouldn't sleep
even one night in peace'

03:31.992 --> 03:33.867
I've given you more than
what you asked

03:33.909 --> 03:34.992
Thank you, brother

03:35.034 --> 03:38.409
If there's any kind of foul play
Esakki will hunt you down and kill you

03:38.450 --> 03:40.034
- Keep an eye
- I'll take care, bro

03:46.284 --> 03:47.409
'Hey! Come'

03:47.992 --> 03:49.742
'What are you glaring at him for?'

03:53.617 --> 03:56.742
Hey! You want the luxury of sleep, huh?

04:01.534 --> 04:02.659
What are you looking at?

04:02.700 --> 04:03.992
Wipe it

04:04.034 --> 04:05.325
Wipe my boots

04:07.200 --> 04:08.825
Pickle you to pieces, rascal!

04:12.575 --> 04:14.409
'All of you, move aside'

04:27.117 --> 04:29.700
Hey you! Can't hit you more than this

04:30.117 --> 04:31.117
Standing

04:31.159 --> 04:33.034
Standing so still
least bit affected!

04:33.075 --> 04:35.867
You are hitting me mercilessly
because someone is paying you

04:35.950 --> 04:39.075
I have to pay you much more
to make you stop hitting me

04:39.807 --> 04:41.948
I am penniless
Hit me all you want

04:42.012 --> 04:43.596
When I have the money

04:43.621 --> 04:45.038
I'll call you then

04:53.398 --> 04:54.981
[phone ringing]

05:00.390 --> 05:01.765
- Who is this?
- 'Brother'

05:01.807 --> 05:03.765
'That boy Bhavani has escaped from jail'

05:03.807 --> 05:06.098
Scumbag! Is this why
I'm spending so lavishly?

05:06.973 --> 05:10.057
I'll deal with you in person
Find him before daybreak

05:11.307 --> 05:12.307
Scuzzbag!

05:26.098 --> 05:27.390
'Don't worry, anna'

05:27.432 --> 05:28.890
I won't harm you

05:28.973 --> 05:32.515
'If I had wanted to, I could have easily
slit your neck when you were asleep'

05:32.598 --> 05:35.765
But I can't be on the run
throughout my life

05:35.890 --> 05:38.265
I came here to request you
to let me lead a normal life

05:38.307 --> 05:39.557
I don't understand

05:42.223 --> 05:43.432
Let me live my own life

05:43.515 --> 05:45.807
What do I gain by releasing you, huh?

05:45.973 --> 05:48.057
Give me a chance
for just this 1 week

05:48.223 --> 05:51.057
I'll give you half of
what I earn this week

05:51.098 --> 05:52.723
'Whichever week I don't pay you'

05:52.765 --> 05:54.890
...stab me on that same day
at that same spot

05:55.182 --> 05:57.182
Fine, I'll take a chance on you

05:57.376 --> 05:59.376
This week is yours, go

06:02.223 --> 06:05.723
How much do you usually pay for a lorry
to cross the check post without a permit?

06:05.765 --> 06:08.598
Only if you cough up Rs 1000 per lorry
you'll be allowed to pass

06:08.640 --> 06:10.348
I'll get the permit slip

06:10.390 --> 06:12.057
Rs 1000 is yours to keep

06:12.265 --> 06:13.973
I want Rs 100 per lorry

06:14.307 --> 06:16.015
If the policemen hassle us?

06:18.890 --> 06:20.390
That's my responsibility

06:29.932 --> 06:32.432
What, I say?
What do you want?

06:44.973 --> 06:47.098
'2002-2003
Register'

06:55.807 --> 06:57.307
Go...go

06:59.515 --> 07:00.765
Move...move

07:01.598 --> 07:02.640
Come, quick

07:02.682 --> 07:04.140
Hey! Wait...wait

07:04.848 --> 07:06.015
Hurry up

07:10.973 --> 07:13.473
If you want the permit slip in your hand

07:13.598 --> 07:15.723
I must get Rs 500 per lorry

07:17.390 --> 07:18.390
Got it?

07:41.557 --> 07:42.640
Whether I'm here or not

07:42.682 --> 07:45.307
...ensure the boys get
their share of booze and fag

07:49.973 --> 07:51.348
'Govt Reformatory'

08:20.057 --> 08:22.682
In a way, only we are
responsible for all this, partner

08:22.765 --> 08:26.015
When we killed his father
we should have burnt him to ashes too

08:26.223 --> 08:31.432
Now he has the gall to contest as head
in the Lorry Drivers' Union Election

08:32.640 --> 08:34.557
How did he amass
this much wealth, bro?

08:35.598 --> 08:39.265
Logu, do you know how many
lorries run under his control?

08:39.932 --> 08:42.182
On top of it, he owns a meat factory

08:42.223 --> 08:43.682
He is into exports too

08:43.890 --> 08:46.640
All this is common news, partner

08:46.973 --> 08:49.265
These boys in the reformatory
for juvenile delinquents

08:49.307 --> 08:52.057
'He uses them to do something
That's where the money flows in'

08:52.098 --> 08:55.057
Some even say he plays proxy
to a minister to launder his money

08:55.265 --> 08:58.182
If he wins this year's Union election

08:59.098 --> 09:02.223
...he will stoop to any level
to avenge his father's murder

09:02.765 --> 09:05.432
Doesn't make sense to spare him
beyond this stage, partner

09:17.973 --> 09:19.265
Talk of the devil!

09:19.307 --> 09:20.723
Close his chapter

09:42.432 --> 09:45.015
Hello, my dear boy
Hindu, Muslim, Christian

09:45.057 --> 09:47.473
You seem to have the charms
of all the Gods around your neck

09:47.515 --> 09:49.265
Each sect endorses
a particular God

09:49.348 --> 09:51.348
One God will save me
when I'm in danger

09:51.432 --> 09:52.723
Minimum guarantee

09:52.765 --> 09:53.807
Philosophy?

09:54.473 --> 09:59.140
Is this the same chap who pleaded
when he was 17 to spare his life?

10:01.682 --> 10:03.765
We need to discuss something
very important with you

10:03.807 --> 10:06.015
You were paying us
on a weekly basis all these years

10:06.057 --> 10:07.348
You can stop it

10:07.473 --> 10:10.473
Instead you can sell all your assets

10:10.515 --> 10:12.932
'Go and earn a living
somewhere outside India'

10:13.223 --> 10:15.223
I felt the same and
wanted to tell you next week

10:15.265 --> 10:16.765
'For how long?
That too every week'

10:16.807 --> 10:19.098
How can I pay tax to you
to ensure my life is not at risk?

10:19.140 --> 10:21.223
That's why I've decided
to stop payment

10:22.432 --> 10:25.640
That decision isn't yours to take, scumbag!

10:25.723 --> 10:27.682
'Just zip your lips
and obey our orders'

10:27.723 --> 10:29.473
I will do only what I feel is right

10:29.515 --> 10:30.682
Hey...dai!

10:31.015 --> 10:33.348
I am well aware of
how dirty your hands are

10:33.682 --> 10:36.015
Making those boys surrender
for the crimes you commit

10:36.057 --> 10:38.598
'Instigating them to kill
We know about all your offenses'

10:38.682 --> 10:41.182
Don't show off your temerity
Just tuck your tail and scoot

10:41.598 --> 10:44.140
Otherwise you will meet your death
in our hands, watch it

10:44.182 --> 10:46.182
[mocking laughter]

10:47.057 --> 10:48.390
[imitating laughter]

10:48.432 --> 10:50.682
Look around you
This is my area

10:50.723 --> 10:51.890
'If I set my heart on it'

10:51.932 --> 10:53.598
Only your lorry will move from here

10:53.640 --> 10:54.682
Not you

10:54.723 --> 10:58.848
I think you are unable to differentiate
working for money and for gratitude?

10:58.890 --> 11:00.765
Shall I show you a sample?

11:04.265 --> 11:07.182
Listen! We have an important
work to do, come here

11:07.973 --> 11:09.432
'He is calling us, come'

11:11.015 --> 11:13.265
- 'Bhavani, da
- Why is he calling us suddenly?'

11:15.682 --> 11:19.432
Whoever kills these 3 men
in this spot will be rewarded

11:19.682 --> 11:20.973
With a prize money

11:22.390 --> 11:23.765
2 million

11:23.890 --> 11:26.015
[burst of amused laughter]

11:28.598 --> 11:30.890
'Do you realize where you are
and what you are blabbering?'

11:30.932 --> 11:32.765
You think I work for anna
with money as motive?

11:32.807 --> 11:34.307
We go back a long way, da

11:34.348 --> 11:36.390
- 3 million
- If you raise it 50%?

11:36.432 --> 11:38.390
- 'He is like my own brother'
- 4 million

11:38.432 --> 11:40.765
Why are you keeping quiet
when he's so arrogant, bro?

11:40.807 --> 11:41.890
Just say 'yes'
I'll kill him-

11:41.932 --> 11:43.015
5 million!

11:44.932 --> 11:47.015
- How dare you rattle off?
- 6 million

11:47.057 --> 11:48.515
Hey! Kill him now

11:48.557 --> 11:51.015
Wait...let us hear our brother out!!

11:51.811 --> 11:53.186
7 million

11:53.348 --> 11:54.973
Wait...wait, bro

11:55.015 --> 11:57.890
I'll go up to the gate and
make sure no one enters this area

11:57.932 --> 11:59.682
- 8 million
- Whaaaat?

11:59.723 --> 12:00.890
Move aside

12:04.390 --> 12:06.307
Then shall we lock
the deal for 8 million?

12:06.348 --> 12:07.598
- Okay, bro
- Are you ready?

12:07.640 --> 12:10.390
We will divide 8 million equally
I'll deal with these 3 men

12:15.348 --> 12:18.598
Now do you know the difference
between greed and gratitude?

12:20.223 --> 12:21.515
Bro, chopper

12:27.973 --> 12:29.140
I don't need this

12:29.432 --> 12:30.932
I'll give you 2 minutes

12:30.973 --> 12:32.473
Kill me if you can

12:34.682 --> 12:35.848
And save yourself

12:52.223 --> 12:53.265
Hey!

12:55.765 --> 12:56.807
Hey!

13:31.307 --> 13:32.348
These boys?

13:32.723 --> 13:33.807
Yes, sir

13:35.182 --> 13:37.723
Post mortem matches the crime scene?

13:37.807 --> 13:39.348
They have done a neat job, sir

13:39.390 --> 13:42.057
Not knowing to drive
they ran over a man

13:42.098 --> 13:43.348
You expect me to buy this?

13:43.390 --> 13:44.973
'Whom are you trying to trick?'

13:45.015 --> 13:47.057
Sir, I'm not a professional driver

13:47.098 --> 13:49.265
I thought I'll try my hand
But turned out fatal

13:49.307 --> 13:50.682
- Right?
- Yes, sir

13:51.848 --> 13:54.265
- 'Do they have a past history?'
- Yes, sir

13:54.307 --> 13:55.765
Pickpocket case, 511

13:55.807 --> 13:58.223
Then 6 months they were in
a Govt reformatory

13:58.265 --> 14:00.390
Now they are in IPC 302
Punished for murder

14:00.432 --> 14:01.765
Is this a reformatory?

14:01.807 --> 14:03.515
Or a criminal training center?

14:03.723 --> 14:06.973
Why do you need this reformatory
that turns a thief into a murderer?

14:07.307 --> 14:09.848
- Call the Observation home staff
- Okay, sir

14:09.890 --> 14:11.432
Sir, he's calling you

14:12.886 --> 14:15.223
Good afternoon, sir
I am the superintendent here

14:15.265 --> 14:18.182
Forget the introduction, when do you
intend employing a regular master?

14:18.223 --> 14:21.140
The boys drive away
any master we appoint

14:21.182 --> 14:23.932
Actually scared of them,
no teacher wants to take up this post

14:23.973 --> 14:25.265
But how can you run a school?

14:25.307 --> 14:27.098
'Not one teacher so far, huh?'

14:27.473 --> 14:29.182
Shocking and shameful!

14:30.103 --> 14:33.436
If there's no master to teach
or guide the students

14:33.478 --> 14:35.353
'...how will they reform, huh?'

14:35.403 --> 14:38.570
'I have personally seen
30-40 cases like this here'

14:39.088 --> 14:40.973
'Superintendent, I'm passing a Govt order'

14:41.015 --> 14:44.557
'Send it to all private, Govt schools
and colleges, to every single institution'

14:44.598 --> 14:45.848
Whole of Tamil Nadu

14:46.015 --> 14:48.432
'You'll find a master
for sure, understand?'

14:48.640 --> 14:49.973
Type out the order

14:57.848 --> 15:00.807
"They call me master
Changes will happen faster"

15:07.432 --> 15:08.515
"His entry spells power"

15:08.557 --> 15:09.890
"Who is our master?
Commander...!"

15:09.932 --> 15:12.890
'St Jeffery College is a truly renowned
educational institution in Chennai'

15:12.932 --> 15:14.890
'Alumni of this college
have carved a name'

15:14.932 --> 15:18.973
'In cinema, politics, advertising and
are celebrities in their own might'

15:19.015 --> 15:21.432
This college has molded innumerable VIPs

15:21.473 --> 15:27.223
'Students are very eager to make this
a very memorable reunion'

15:27.265 --> 15:29.557
Do you want to know why?
Come along with me

15:32.473 --> 15:33.848
Hi...Ramya

15:34.057 --> 15:35.765
- Hi, nice to meet you
- Same here

15:35.807 --> 15:37.390
I've spoken to you over the phone

15:37.432 --> 15:38.640
- Oh! That was you?
- Yeah

15:38.682 --> 15:39.926
Okay...okay

15:39.952 --> 15:42.119
- What's your full name?
- Charulatha Prasad

15:42.145 --> 15:44.687
Come, let me introduce you to everyone

15:44.723 --> 15:47.640
- This college has a decorum
- Students are capable of doing it

15:47.682 --> 15:50.765
Their plan is to ruin our image when
the minister arrives as our chief guest

15:50.807 --> 15:53.348
'If this issue leaks,
your college reputation is at stake'

15:53.390 --> 15:55.515
You want to take further action

15:55.557 --> 15:57.765
- Do so after the minister leaves
- This is well planned

15:57.807 --> 15:59.723
'Sri, stop this cat & mouse game'

15:59.765 --> 16:02.140
- You had better confess the truth
- Trust me, sir

16:02.182 --> 16:03.932
- Isn't JD responsible?
- No, sir

16:03.973 --> 16:05.307
I swear, no, sir

16:05.348 --> 16:07.598
Then who is the culprit?
Your father...?

16:07.932 --> 16:09.765
Everyone knows about Savitha's trauma

16:09.807 --> 16:12.075
I know how those 2 scumbags
sexually harassed her-

16:12.127 --> 16:13.210
Hey! Mind your words

16:13.252 --> 16:14.668
Spit that gum first

16:16.890 --> 16:17.807
I said throw it out

16:17.848 --> 16:19.723
I'll trash it as soon as
it loses its sweetness

16:19.765 --> 16:20.848
Don't act smart

16:21.504 --> 16:23.390
The two noble souls
who sexually harassed her

16:23.432 --> 16:24.973
You suspended them for 1 week

16:25.015 --> 16:27.390
Knowing it was inadequate
we even complained to the police

16:27.432 --> 16:29.848
But they took us for a ride
without taking any action

16:29.926 --> 16:32.182
Only then we knew Aadith's dad
is a rich businessman

16:32.223 --> 16:34.640
I think he has planned
to send them off to Canada

16:34.760 --> 16:36.468
That's why I took the boys

16:36.494 --> 16:38.327
'...to his house
to find out his plan'

16:40.489 --> 16:42.780
'Hello, sir, they haven't
left the house as yet'

16:42.822 --> 16:44.072
'I think they are still inside'

16:44.114 --> 16:46.780
'But it's evident they have
hatched a plot to escape'

16:46.822 --> 16:49.489
'Strangers keep walking into their house'

16:49.572 --> 16:51.905
'Sir, I can hear their voices
I think they are coming out'

16:51.947 --> 16:53.489
- 'Take care, son
- Don't worry, pa'

16:53.530 --> 16:55.947
- Be safe
- I'll call as soon as I reach

16:55.989 --> 16:57.405
'This is the duo'

16:57.489 --> 16:58.864
'Call after you reach the airport'

16:58.905 --> 17:00.155
Go...go...go

17:00.739 --> 17:01.864
Let's follow them

17:04.030 --> 17:06.072
Both of them have left home, sir

17:06.114 --> 17:08.489
Aadith and Rahul are in a taxi
They just crossed Ashok Nagar

17:08.530 --> 17:10.822
'Along with our boys
I am following them, sir'

17:10.864 --> 17:12.447
- Where are you, bro?
- 'At a signal'

17:12.488 --> 17:14.696
- Which signal?
- Jafferkhanpet

17:14.739 --> 17:15.905
Ask him the bus #

17:16.239 --> 17:17.405
- Which bus?
- '70 V'

17:17.489 --> 17:18.447
Bus #, bro?

17:18.489 --> 17:19.780
70, V

17:19.822 --> 17:21.864
It's coming close to you
Waiting at the signal now

17:21.905 --> 17:23.239
'Bro...look this side'

17:23.280 --> 17:24.822
I've spotted you
Come on, hurry up

17:24.864 --> 17:26.364
'Look, it's that bus'

17:26.405 --> 17:27.572
Quick!

17:31.989 --> 17:33.572
- 'Get in'
- Move

17:33.614 --> 17:35.447
Both of them got into bus # 70 V, sir

17:35.489 --> 17:37.905
'Bus # TN 01 AN 1184'

17:37.947 --> 17:40.155
'Bus has crossed Jafferkhanpet signa-'

17:40.864 --> 17:42.405
Why did he cut my call?

17:44.864 --> 17:47.322
"Got the man with the plan right here"

17:47.405 --> 17:49.614
"Bringin' swag with the man right here"

17:49.655 --> 17:51.780
[mobile ringing]

17:51.989 --> 17:54.280
"Yeah, clap for me, man, right here"

17:54.364 --> 17:56.822
"Got the man with the plan right here"

17:56.864 --> 17:59.114
"Bringin' swag with the man right here"

17:59.209 --> 18:01.584
"Livin' up and sippin on beer"

18:01.614 --> 18:03.864
"Yeah, clap for me, man, right here"

18:05.864 --> 18:07.905
"Hey! No matter what they say"

18:07.947 --> 18:09.447
"Master the blaster"

18:10.572 --> 18:12.697
"Hey! No matter what they do"

18:12.739 --> 18:14.197
"Mr Master the Blaster"

18:14.239 --> 18:15.280
"Riddim"

18:15.322 --> 18:17.364
"Hey! No matter what they say"

18:17.447 --> 18:18.489
"Master the blaster"

18:18.530 --> 18:19.989
"Yeah! Master the blaster"

18:20.030 --> 18:22.197
"Hey! No matter what they do"

18:22.239 --> 18:23.572
"Mr Master the Blaster"

18:23.614 --> 18:25.614
"Got the man with the plan right here"

18:25.655 --> 18:27.405
"Bringin' swag with the man right here"

18:27.447 --> 18:30.322
"Repeat!
Livin' up and sippin on beer"

18:30.405 --> 18:32.739
"Yeah, clap for me man, right here"

18:32.822 --> 18:35.197
"Got the man with the plan right here"

18:35.239 --> 18:36.989
"Bringin' swag with the man right here"

18:37.030 --> 18:39.947
"Repeat!
Livin' up and sippin on beer"

18:39.989 --> 18:42.447
"Yeah, clap for me, man, right here"

18:42.489 --> 18:43.947
"Sound the alarm"

18:44.822 --> 18:48.989
"Yeah! Give it up for my man JD
settin' fire to the screen"

18:57.919 --> 18:59.127
No problem at all, bro

18:59.169 --> 19:00.460
I've informed our boys

19:00.502 --> 19:02.085
They are inside the airport

19:02.127 --> 19:04.460
Don't worry at all
All loopholes covered

19:08.002 --> 19:09.210
"He spells power boldly"

19:09.252 --> 19:10.627
"Who is he?
Thalapathy!"

19:37.044 --> 19:38.460
Come, let's go

19:39.419 --> 19:40.419
Not you

19:40.460 --> 19:42.335
- Come
- Hey!

19:43.006 --> 19:44.215
Throw him out

19:50.585 --> 19:51.585
Who is that?

19:51.981 --> 19:53.147
Professor

19:57.085 --> 19:59.210
'Bro, get up
Come...come'

19:59.335 --> 20:00.669
Hurry up

20:03.252 --> 20:05.085
'Hey driver, don't stop the bus'

20:05.127 --> 20:06.502
Go...go...keep going

20:06.585 --> 20:07.960
'Don't stop, keep moving'

20:10.877 --> 20:11.960
[amused snigger]

20:24.502 --> 20:25.669
'Stop...stop'

20:25.710 --> 20:26.835
'Stop, man'

20:26.877 --> 20:28.835
'Let's get off
Come soon'

20:39.169 --> 20:41.210
'They got down from the bus and ran'

20:41.252 --> 20:42.502
Thank god he came in his bike

20:42.544 --> 20:44.169
- It wasn't him
- Sorry, sir, he came

20:44.710 --> 20:45.752
Sir, come

20:46.127 --> 20:48.794
'In all this confusion
they ran into the Metro station'

20:49.460 --> 20:50.835
Give me the token

20:51.669 --> 20:53.127
Come fast

20:53.794 --> 20:55.002
'Get in, quick'

21:30.669 --> 21:31.752
Looks cool, eh?

21:31.794 --> 21:35.127
I never got a chance to take a Metro train
from when it started operating

21:36.294 --> 21:37.419
Thanks, boys

21:39.119 --> 21:40.119
Hey...!

21:40.544 --> 21:42.544
I plan to stab a master here

21:43.377 --> 21:45.002
Brave hearts, continue the ride

21:45.044 --> 21:46.544
Fainthearted, alight

21:46.960 --> 21:48.127
Girls...girls

21:48.210 --> 21:49.335
I'll collect it later

21:49.377 --> 21:51.335
'If you move a bit,
I can go there and watch'

21:51.377 --> 21:52.419
Thanks, sir

21:54.585 --> 21:56.002
[smug chuckle]

22:48.978 --> 22:49.853
What?

23:01.536 --> 23:05.869
How are college students and
'dhoti' clad politicians connected?

23:13.252 --> 23:15.127
Airport is close by

23:15.169 --> 23:16.833
Catch an auto or something and go

23:16.880 --> 23:18.796
Don't wait here
Hurry up

23:23.252 --> 23:25.502
They rushed out and
got into a share auto

23:25.544 --> 23:28.210
Turned out to be our friend
Jameel anna's auto, I got in too!

23:28.252 --> 23:30.794
'Easy-peasy that's where they got caught'

23:37.127 --> 23:39.210
- Escape to Canada, right?
- Yes, sir

23:39.252 --> 23:42.002
'Friends encircled and took them
to the police station, right?'

23:42.044 --> 23:43.169
Yes, sir

23:43.627 --> 23:45.585
So you were responsible
for everything

23:45.627 --> 23:48.294
- Yes, sir
- JD had nothing to do with this?

23:48.335 --> 23:49.960
We swear, nothing at all, sir

23:50.002 --> 23:51.044
'Sir'

23:51.085 --> 23:53.710
Those 2 boys swear
your teacher JD was behind this

23:53.752 --> 23:55.919
- These students are lying
- Of course I know, sir

23:55.960 --> 23:57.210
JD is the culprit

23:57.252 --> 23:59.294
- Who is JD?
- 'He is playing up with their support'

23:59.335 --> 24:01.585
- I'll tell you, long story
- 'One day he'll get caught'

24:01.627 --> 24:02.794
'That will be his doomsday'

24:02.835 --> 24:04.169
Minister has arrived

24:04.210 --> 24:06.294
If you are ready, we can
escort him to the auditorium

24:06.335 --> 24:07.460
Come...come

24:07.502 --> 24:08.877
Sir, you please sit

24:09.085 --> 24:11.335
- I'll be back in 10 minutes
- I'll wait

24:11.377 --> 24:12.877
- Serve him tea
- Carry on

24:12.919 --> 24:14.210
2 minutes, sir
I'll be right back

24:14.252 --> 24:15.585
Not picking your call, huh?

24:15.627 --> 24:17.210
It's ringing but he isn't picking

24:17.252 --> 24:19.919
Same-same when student
and now as master also?

24:19.960 --> 24:22.252
Shut up, da
Vanathi, didn't you try?

24:22.377 --> 24:23.585
I asked the students

24:23.627 --> 24:25.460
- What did they say?
- He has been suspended

24:25.502 --> 24:28.419
If you had told us earlier, we could
have gone in person and brought him

24:28.460 --> 24:30.335
He must be very busy, try again

24:30.377 --> 24:32.752
'We relish the 'rajma' happil-'

24:32.794 --> 24:35.085
[mobile ringing]

24:35.127 --> 24:37.419
"Livin' up and sippin on beer"

24:37.460 --> 24:39.919
"Yeah, clap for me, man, right here"

24:39.960 --> 24:41.960
Uncle, he's our Principal
Anbiah Samuel

24:42.002 --> 24:43.752
Welcome, sir
This is our vice principal

24:46.794 --> 24:47.919
'Ramya?'

24:47.960 --> 24:50.544
If that student is such a troublemaker

24:50.585 --> 24:52.669
...why not just dismiss him?

24:52.710 --> 24:55.669
Then he should have
got dismissed 20 years ago!

24:55.924 --> 24:57.049
I don't get it

24:57.835 --> 24:59.044
JD isn't a student, my dear

24:59.085 --> 25:00.085
Professor!

25:00.127 --> 25:02.710
- Whaaat?
- Dean of student affairs

25:03.377 --> 25:05.044
'First of all
we welcome you all'

25:05.085 --> 25:07.085
'Good morning one and all present here'

25:07.127 --> 25:10.085
'Our honorable chief guest
Manavai R Gauthaman'

25:10.127 --> 25:12.627
'Respected dignitaries on the dais'

25:12.669 --> 25:13.710
'What happened?'

25:26.835 --> 25:29.960
Sir, students are refusing
to come from the back stage

25:31.085 --> 25:33.210
It seems you said this function
won't go on without JD?

25:33.252 --> 25:35.627
Then what, sir? We kept
telling you he is not to blame

25:35.669 --> 25:37.169
'You've suspended him for 2 weeks'

25:37.210 --> 25:39.710
Any other day it's fine, sir
This alumni meet is only for him

25:39.752 --> 25:42.335
How can he not be here, sir?
Nothing will happen without him

25:42.377 --> 25:44.252
Are you the human rights activist?

25:45.835 --> 25:47.085
Just you wait!

25:47.127 --> 25:49.585
Sir, the minister has been
waiting for a long time

25:49.627 --> 25:51.919
- Please bear with us
- He cancelled so many appointments

25:51.960 --> 25:54.710
- Start the program
- I'll talk to them and join you

25:57.710 --> 26:00.794
Om Shanti! Om Shanti!
Peace in speech and spirit

26:00.835 --> 26:03.085
- Call JD
- You suspended him and asking me to call?

26:03.127 --> 26:05.335
- You call him
- I don't know his #

26:05.377 --> 26:06.377
Call him, dude

26:06.419 --> 26:08.085
Call before he changes his mind

26:09.419 --> 26:11.710
[humming a song]

26:12.252 --> 26:14.169
[mobile ringing]

26:14.544 --> 26:17.169
"Livin' up and sippin on beer"

26:17.577 --> 26:19.661
Hello...huh...JD

26:20.210 --> 26:22.627
This is Principal...Samuel here

26:22.669 --> 26:24.127
JD sir is fast asleep

26:24.169 --> 26:25.127
Call later

26:25.169 --> 26:26.585
Principal Anbiah Samuel

26:26.627 --> 26:29.627
Anbu, your name can mean love but
he won't get up to hear your loving words

26:29.669 --> 26:32.419
- Guzzled down 3 or 4 bottles
- 'Can you wake him up or not?'

26:33.044 --> 26:34.210
No chance, love

26:37.627 --> 26:38.544
Hey!

26:38.920 --> 26:40.004
He's drunk

26:41.127 --> 26:42.127
What can I do?

26:42.169 --> 26:44.794
Will you ask your Education Minister
to wait for half an hour?

26:44.835 --> 26:46.085
We'll go and get him

26:47.044 --> 26:48.127
- Whaat?
- Do it

26:52.624 --> 26:54.541
- What, da?
- Not budging an inch

26:59.585 --> 27:01.044
Is this how you drum-roll?

27:01.085 --> 27:03.002
Getting paid right?
Bump it, fellows

27:07.335 --> 27:08.960
Rock & roll, man

27:09.044 --> 27:10.835
This is it
This is what we want

27:10.919 --> 27:12.585
Ready, da
Come on, da

27:12.669 --> 27:14.585
"Master is coming, move aside"

27:19.627 --> 27:21.127
Hey stop...stop

27:22.252 --> 27:23.710
Lift him

27:24.627 --> 27:26.794
Heave-ho!

27:44.085 --> 27:45.127
Speed up!

27:52.002 --> 27:53.960
- Sir, good morning
- Good morning

27:54.002 --> 27:55.127
Tea, sir

28:06.252 --> 28:09.085
"The moment our bro steps in
it's like an atom bomb exploding"

28:16.127 --> 28:18.960
- Did they really invite me?
- Sir, why this doubt?

28:19.002 --> 28:20.627
'I swear they asked you to come'

28:21.835 --> 28:23.460
Bro, beat the drum

28:34.678 --> 28:35.970
"Master coming!"

28:36.004 --> 28:37.004
'Move aside!'

28:41.377 --> 28:42.752
'Rock & roll!'

28:48.127 --> 28:50.960
"Deliberately if you make trouble"

28:51.044 --> 28:53.877
"It will boomerang on you centuple"

28:53.960 --> 28:56.669
"If you jeer or sneer at us"

28:56.721 --> 28:59.471
"Mind you, you'll be limbless"

29:01.827 --> 29:02.869
'Zazzorific!'

29:04.627 --> 29:05.835
Aiyo!

29:09.710 --> 29:11.377
"Tell topsy turvy
Yell curvy scurvy"

29:21.419 --> 29:23.044
"Rock & roll
Heart & soul"

29:32.252 --> 29:34.835
"Split their ears, no matter
Scare them to scatter"

29:45.752 --> 29:46.794
'Move aside'

30:01.788 --> 30:02.913
Aiyo!

30:30.127 --> 30:33.252
"The second our bro steps in
it's like an atom bomb exploding"

30:47.002 --> 30:49.585
"Hit the drum harder
Scare them to scatter"

30:59.127 --> 31:01.044
"Master, coming"

31:02.127 --> 31:03.794
Bent double, sir?

31:03.960 --> 31:05.585
- Where is the ID card?
- I have it, sir

31:05.627 --> 31:07.252
- First wear it and go inside
- Done

31:15.252 --> 31:17.877
'We are all soaked in celebration mode'

31:20.252 --> 31:21.252
Let's go

31:25.210 --> 31:27.835
- 'Sit with us, da'
- Is he a professor?

31:28.044 --> 31:29.210
Suspended professor

31:29.252 --> 31:30.544
'What is his name?'

31:30.585 --> 31:31.627
'JD'

31:33.210 --> 31:34.169
Start the program

31:34.210 --> 31:35.794
Sir, 1 minute
Let me speak

31:35.835 --> 31:36.835
Sir-

31:37.169 --> 31:38.544
Give this to JD sir

31:39.919 --> 31:41.377
'I've attended
many college functions'

31:41.419 --> 31:43.669
- Wear your ID card
- 'Witnessed many gatherings'

31:43.710 --> 31:46.044
'But I've never seen a crowd like this'

31:46.377 --> 31:48.377
Because the entire crowd here

31:48.669 --> 31:50.669
More than the anchor of the show

31:50.710 --> 31:52.627
'They are celebrating
the man seated below'

31:52.669 --> 31:54.127
'It is no mean achievement'

31:54.169 --> 31:56.752
'If he is getting this kind of
reception among students'

31:56.794 --> 32:00.210
'Then he must be a dedicated
and focused professor'

32:00.252 --> 32:01.544
'If he himself is like this...'

32:01.585 --> 32:03.710
- 'Imagine his students'
- Why try all these gimmicks?

32:03.752 --> 32:05.127
'Must be good as gold'

32:05.794 --> 32:08.002
'First give this man
a big round of applause'

32:09.169 --> 32:11.252
To get a professor like him

32:11.544 --> 32:13.460
You and your college
must be truly blessed

32:13.502 --> 32:14.934
Your eyes are red
Wear this shade

32:14.986 --> 32:16.861
'This most revered master'

32:16.903 --> 32:19.986
'I would like him to come up
to the dais and say a few words'

32:21.252 --> 32:22.294
'I am calling you, sir'

32:22.335 --> 32:23.335
Please come

32:24.882 --> 32:26.216
Come up and speak

32:26.919 --> 32:28.835
Hey...! Where are you going?

32:28.877 --> 32:30.794
Wait, let me tell a mini story

32:30.835 --> 32:32.335
Did you look at your shoes?

32:33.044 --> 32:34.794
Instead of being humiliated, sit down

32:34.835 --> 32:36.210
If you get up once more-

32:36.252 --> 32:38.169
Please take your seat

32:40.127 --> 32:41.294
JD is our-

32:42.460 --> 32:45.585
Management and staff
are completely against JD

32:45.856 --> 32:47.731
But students celebrate him

32:48.478 --> 32:49.561
I don't get this

32:49.919 --> 32:52.377
He has gone out of his way
for students' welfare

32:52.419 --> 32:54.085
Students revere him as their true hero

32:54.127 --> 32:56.210
Reason enough for
the management to dislike him

32:56.252 --> 32:58.919
Secondly after 6:00 p.m
our hero will be totally sloshed!

33:05.877 --> 33:07.627
- 'Sorry
- Sorry, guys'

33:29.710 --> 33:30.877
Hello, sir

33:31.585 --> 33:32.835
Good morning, sir

33:40.085 --> 33:41.085
Careful, sir

33:44.877 --> 33:46.210
- Sorry...sorry
- It's okay

33:48.960 --> 33:49.960
Hi...hi

33:50.002 --> 33:51.544
Your classroom is at that end

33:51.585 --> 33:53.044
Oh! Good morning

33:53.085 --> 33:55.919
'What is his flashback sob story
to get sloshed every day?'

33:55.960 --> 33:57.085
Don't ask him that alone

33:57.127 --> 34:00.210
If he gets a gullible idiot, he'll reel off
a Mani Ratnam classic as his own!

34:00.252 --> 34:02.960
Fell head over heels, chased her
in the college, bus, everywhere

34:03.002 --> 34:07.169
She also reciprocated and one day
we were happily sitting in a coffee shop

34:07.210 --> 34:08.294
Her father walked in!

34:08.335 --> 34:10.710
- Aiyo! Did you get caught?
- Wait, akka

34:10.752 --> 34:11.960
Her father's name

34:12.002 --> 34:13.210
Mr Chandramouli!

34:13.252 --> 34:15.169
We were both neighbors
in Rainbow Colony

34:15.210 --> 34:17.085
I was in 8G
She was in 7G

34:17.127 --> 34:18.252
India is here

34:18.960 --> 34:20.669
America is right here

34:20.877 --> 34:24.585
I took my guitar and left, my love for
Anjalai was as strong as 1000 elephants!

34:24.627 --> 34:26.752
We climbed up straight to
the top of the mountain

34:26.794 --> 34:29.169
We decided to jump
counting 1 to 5

34:29.210 --> 34:31.669
My bad luck, I got stuck
in a tree and escaped death

34:32.002 --> 34:33.044
What, da?

34:33.210 --> 34:35.169
Her head hit a boulder and she died

34:35.210 --> 34:37.419
- That's a Kamal classic...don't bug me
- Hey...listen

34:37.460 --> 34:38.919
Too much filmy imagination

34:39.710 --> 34:41.419
Okay, which department is he in?

34:41.460 --> 34:44.210
He studied in this same college
He finished M.Phil Psychology here

34:44.252 --> 34:46.752
'Now he teaches
Personality Development'

34:46.794 --> 34:49.002
May I request you all to please stand up?

34:49.981 --> 34:52.689
I said...stand...up

34:52.746 --> 34:56.037
Now I intend checking
if your mind and body are focused

34:56.127 --> 34:57.335
We are hearing

34:58.746 --> 34:59.871
But not listening

34:59.897 --> 35:03.200
Students don't listen to their teachers
Teachers don't listen to their students

35:03.252 --> 35:04.294
Now

35:04.335 --> 35:05.585
RUN

35:06.002 --> 35:07.710
Run...run...run

35:07.752 --> 35:08.794
WATER!

35:10.012 --> 35:11.178
Electricity...!

35:13.127 --> 35:17.085
Children don't listen to their parents
Parents don't listen to their children

35:17.127 --> 35:18.252
And finally

35:18.419 --> 35:20.536
No one listens to the people!

35:20.587 --> 35:23.462
Whatever I tell you now
repeat it verbatim

35:23.512 --> 35:24.512
But

35:24.939 --> 35:26.189
Do just the opposite

35:26.335 --> 35:27.919
Jump in

35:27.960 --> 35:29.585
Jump left

35:29.627 --> 35:31.585
Jump right
Dai...dai...!

35:31.627 --> 35:33.002
Now on the starboard

35:33.720 --> 35:35.012
Faster...faster...faster

35:35.054 --> 35:37.471
Now close your eyes and freeze

35:43.294 --> 35:44.794
Class disperse

35:46.463 --> 35:47.713
Getting late for my class

35:47.754 --> 35:49.545
- We'll meet at lunch
- Okay, sure

35:54.794 --> 35:56.169
'Let me repeat this'

35:56.210 --> 35:58.627
That scoundrel Bhavani is
responsible for all this

35:58.669 --> 36:02.002
He finished off his opponents contesting
in our Union election one by one

36:02.044 --> 36:03.960
I know his history A to Z

36:04.002 --> 36:07.210
Gurumurthy, whether these people
understand it or not, hope you do

36:08.044 --> 36:10.044
I have been saying this
right from the beginning

36:10.085 --> 36:11.085
Who endorsed my view?

36:11.127 --> 36:13.752
With the help of juveniles
he is into all criminal activities

36:13.794 --> 36:15.002
Has the cat got your tongue?!

36:15.044 --> 36:17.627
- Tell them
- Yov! We know this alread-

36:29.252 --> 36:30.419
Vanakkam, anna

36:31.585 --> 36:32.877
Damn you!

36:32.999 --> 36:35.124
Are you such a big shot, huh?

36:35.658 --> 36:38.366
If you kill him, will you get his post?

36:38.564 --> 36:40.356
- Let me see
- No, bro

36:40.413 --> 36:42.663
Why are you so mad at me?
I'm like a brother to you

36:42.720 --> 36:44.053
Whatever it is
let's talk it over

36:44.087 --> 36:45.920
Any need for me to talk to you?

36:45.970 --> 36:47.053
I'll close your chapter!

36:47.103 --> 36:48.145
Get the car ready

36:48.193 --> 36:50.193
Bro, will a problem
be solved if we fight?

36:50.252 --> 36:52.544
Will murder solve the problem?
Let's discuss it amicably

36:52.585 --> 36:56.210
I'll use the same juvenile delinquents
you use as tool to finish you off!

36:56.252 --> 36:57.210
Want to wait and watch?

36:57.252 --> 36:59.085
I'm like one of them
You watched me grow

36:59.127 --> 37:01.044
- Wait, bro
- You peed in your pants scared of me

37:01.085 --> 37:02.585
You think you're my equal now?

37:02.627 --> 37:04.294
Whatever it is, let's talk it over

37:04.335 --> 37:06.710
I am much younger than you
But pay heed to my words

37:06.752 --> 37:07.877
Don't go, br-

37:08.502 --> 37:09.627
'Oh my God!'

37:09.752 --> 37:11.085
Gone, anna?

37:11.169 --> 37:12.919
'Catch that lorry driver'

37:18.960 --> 37:20.085
So sad!

37:20.127 --> 37:21.210
You were eye witnesses

37:21.252 --> 37:22.752
What did I do?

37:22.794 --> 37:25.210
If I had walked out talking to him
I would've shared his fate

37:25.252 --> 37:27.210
Impossible for a human
to time this so perfectly

37:27.252 --> 37:29.044
I pray to all Gods thrice daily

37:29.085 --> 37:31.252
So God has saved me
and punished him

37:31.460 --> 37:32.877
'He was a good soul!'

37:35.502 --> 37:38.085
To conduct Students' election
in our college this year

37:38.127 --> 37:42.960
University Grants Commission has granted
permission, but I opposed it strictly

37:43.044 --> 37:47.377
That's why for a mere formality
I need all your opinions

37:47.919 --> 37:49.835
Why we don't want election

37:49.877 --> 37:51.127
For the records

37:51.710 --> 37:53.585
I somehow feel it is unnecessary, sir

37:53.627 --> 37:54.919
'Semester is fast approaching'

37:54.960 --> 37:57.044
'In the current scenario
why do we need an election?'

37:57.085 --> 37:59.333
'Sir, if this is happening
some other issues will create'

37:59.373 --> 38:01.832
- I don't think they are fit for elections
- Exactly

38:01.960 --> 38:03.752
'In my honest opinion, no'

38:03.794 --> 38:06.210
'I have no issues with
the day college students'

38:06.252 --> 38:08.419
'I am a little apprehensive
about the evening batch'

38:08.460 --> 38:09.710
Thanks, Ramya

38:09.752 --> 38:10.835
Charulatha, your opinion?

38:10.877 --> 38:14.002
It's only been 2 weeks
since I joined, sir

38:14.127 --> 38:16.752
So if I voice my opinion
I don't know if it will be right

38:16.794 --> 38:18.377
Come on, what's there?

38:19.419 --> 38:20.710
- No, sir
- Hey!

38:20.752 --> 38:23.044
- Why is JD sir keeping quiet?
- That's right?

38:23.127 --> 38:25.960
- He'll wait to get a good point
- 'I don't think election is a good idea'

38:26.002 --> 38:29.460
Sir, to be on the safe side
ask JD his opinion

38:32.377 --> 38:34.627
'JD, tell us your opinion'

38:39.794 --> 38:41.877
What is your opinion, JD?

38:41.919 --> 38:44.085
- What day was yesterday?
- Thursday

38:44.127 --> 38:45.752
Thursday is his day off, da

38:45.794 --> 38:47.794
- 'Professor JD'
- He would have been piss drunk

38:47.835 --> 38:50.252
- Come...come
- Hey! Careful

38:51.002 --> 38:52.127
'JD...?'

38:53.835 --> 38:55.210
SIR!

38:55.252 --> 38:56.377
Emergency, sir

38:56.419 --> 38:57.460
What are you doing here?

38:57.502 --> 38:59.377
Let me give this phone to Rosie madam

38:59.419 --> 39:01.210
Her husband fell off his bike

39:01.252 --> 39:02.502
'What the hell are you doing?'

39:02.544 --> 39:03.585
I will expel you

39:03.627 --> 39:06.210
- Let her just talk to him
- What happened, Abdul?

39:06.419 --> 39:07.419
'Wake up, sir'

39:07.460 --> 39:08.919
Don't switch off your phone

39:08.960 --> 39:10.044
Talk to him

39:10.169 --> 39:11.669
- Poor husband
- 1 minute, sir

39:11.710 --> 39:14.044
They are objecting to elections
Support us, sir

39:14.585 --> 39:15.669
- Sorry, sir
- Get out

39:15.710 --> 39:17.252
- Useless fellow!
- Thank you, sir

39:18.710 --> 39:21.127
JD, what is your opinion
about conducting elections?

39:21.169 --> 39:23.669
Election is essential, that's all

39:24.294 --> 39:27.085
- I thought as much
- 'He will say something meaningless, sir'

39:27.127 --> 39:30.960
If we announce a students' election
all of them will be thinking of only that

39:31.002 --> 39:33.752
Not one of them will study
nor will anyone attend any class

39:33.794 --> 39:37.210
Correct, what will they learn
by conducting students' election?

39:37.710 --> 39:39.502
Why encourage politics in college?

39:40.044 --> 39:41.294
Matthew sir

39:41.752 --> 39:43.377
What is 'politics', sir?

39:43.710 --> 39:45.377
Sir, I don't wish to talk to you

39:45.877 --> 39:47.460
Is that so?
But I wish to speak

39:47.502 --> 39:48.502
I'm coming

39:51.502 --> 39:52.544
Sir

39:53.335 --> 39:56.085
First a student should know
'politics' means service

39:56.127 --> 39:59.752
Only if our students learn about election,
canvassing, leadership in college

39:59.794 --> 40:02.877
...they will have an awareness about
state, central elections for the future

40:02.919 --> 40:05.710
College students are our first time voters

40:06.127 --> 40:07.502
Only if (s)he is allowed to think

40:07.544 --> 40:09.710
A new leader will emerge
for the next generation

40:09.752 --> 40:12.502
To mould as a good leader
or to choose the right leader

40:12.544 --> 40:14.669
...they will acquire
both tact and discretion

40:14.710 --> 40:16.002
For someone to-

40:16.319 --> 40:18.944
They will stick posters all over
and spoil the walls with graffiti

40:18.970 --> 40:20.887
Then claim ownership
over the walls and fight

40:20.913 --> 40:23.038
Doesn't all this happen
in normal elections?

40:23.118 --> 40:24.118
Sit down, sir

40:25.044 --> 40:27.877
Aren't these normal issues
that crop up in general elections?

40:27.919 --> 40:30.335
So can we decide to
abolish elections in our country?

40:30.377 --> 40:33.752
'We have grown up with this culture of
poster, banner, fanfare, still follow it'

40:33.794 --> 40:37.169
If students should know
the do's and don'ts of poster etc

40:37.210 --> 40:39.252
...we must conduct
elections in college

40:39.419 --> 40:41.085
Only then he will be
a good example outside

40:41.127 --> 40:45.252
'If our culture of bribing with 'biriyani'
booze and big bucks should change'

40:45.377 --> 40:47.752
...students should know
the ins and outs of politics

40:47.835 --> 40:48.835
Okay

40:49.210 --> 40:50.919
Let's assume what you're saying is right

40:50.960 --> 40:55.877
Who is responsible if students resort
to violence or damage college property?

40:55.919 --> 40:58.002
Sir, nothing of that sort will happen

40:58.044 --> 41:00.752
If you are proved wrong
will you leave this college?

41:00.835 --> 41:02.877
Will you resign, huh?

41:03.377 --> 41:04.710
We'll see if it happens

41:04.919 --> 41:07.127
Then you be the presiding officer

41:07.210 --> 41:08.877
And conduct this election

41:09.210 --> 41:11.085
If any problem crops up

41:11.127 --> 41:13.585
Sign an affidavit
you will leave this college

41:19.544 --> 41:22.585
Coming June 25th
Students' elections

41:22.669 --> 41:24.419
[loud cheering]

41:26.335 --> 41:29.127
I haven't seen him conduct
an election as a master

41:29.169 --> 41:31.919
'But I've seen him
do the same as a student'

41:36.502 --> 41:37.544
Pccht!

41:41.169 --> 41:42.460
Shake your hands

41:48.169 --> 41:50.127
This is the wall of democracy

41:50.169 --> 41:51.835
Your rules & regulations

41:56.085 --> 41:58.044
'Gym facilities free for all students'

41:58.127 --> 42:00.627
'Meat will be served for all in the hostel'

42:00.752 --> 42:04.377
Good orators have become able leaders
You should speak up more boldly, Savi

42:04.419 --> 42:06.919
'Instead of finding faults
with your rival and campaigning'

42:06.960 --> 42:09.085
'...ask for votes
listing your reforms'

42:09.835 --> 42:12.335
Tear every single poster, dude

42:12.377 --> 42:15.335
Posters and banners should be stuck
or erected in their allocated places

42:15.377 --> 42:17.544
'Even if there's a small brawl
among the students'

42:17.585 --> 42:19.002
'...election will be canceled'

42:20.252 --> 42:22.960
You pull back and fire

42:23.002 --> 42:24.002
Cheers!

42:24.044 --> 42:26.210
'Our total strength is 5500 students, sir'

42:26.252 --> 42:28.544
We have divided them into 10 categories

42:28.919 --> 42:29.960
What is this column?

42:30.002 --> 42:32.544
That is religion & caste category

42:32.960 --> 42:34.335
Let's avoid that

42:34.377 --> 42:36.794
Only if we delete it here

42:36.835 --> 42:39.002
It won't tag along with us terribly

42:41.502 --> 42:44.585
Hey! How much longer do you intend
drinking like this and roaming around?

42:44.669 --> 42:46.377
Why yell at me
for no reason?

42:46.419 --> 42:48.752
Will I yell at you
if you are steady on your feet?

42:50.585 --> 42:52.710
- I am sober
- Is that so?

42:54.210 --> 42:56.044
Hit an arrow
anywhere on this board

42:56.085 --> 42:57.919
I'll agree you are
sober and steady

42:58.169 --> 43:00.169
Machi, aim for the bull's eye

43:10.627 --> 43:12.460
Rs 1 lakh to students
in each department

43:12.502 --> 43:14.044
Cheers!

43:14.794 --> 43:17.335
'I have a fair amount of
experience in counselling'

43:17.377 --> 43:21.210
If you can tell me the reason
I can do my level best to help you

43:21.252 --> 43:24.085
Earlier on...when I was jobless

43:25.377 --> 43:27.877
I was hanging around
in a tiles company in Rajasthan

43:27.919 --> 43:29.252
- Oh!
- At that time

43:29.287 --> 43:31.996
A girl lost her bag in the train

43:32.419 --> 43:34.919
I found it and sent it to her

43:35.044 --> 43:37.252
She liked me for the effort I took

43:38.085 --> 43:41.960
She and I became pen pals and
we built a 'Fort of love' just for us

43:43.085 --> 43:45.627
Then when she knew
I was in Rajasthan

43:45.669 --> 43:47.419
For my sake that girl
took extra pains

43:47.460 --> 43:51.335
Embroidered, knitted
a sweater and sent it to me

43:51.377 --> 43:52.960
Sweater in Rajasthan!

43:55.252 --> 43:56.419
True that?

44:05.585 --> 44:07.585
'Whenever you have a problem
and you come to me'

44:07.627 --> 44:09.669
'Even if it's midnight
I'll be there for you'

44:09.710 --> 44:12.710
Why should we create problems
and end up in the police station?

44:12.752 --> 44:14.252
Beverages free in the canteen

44:14.710 --> 44:16.377
Aqua training access free

44:16.419 --> 44:19.710
You will have campus interviews
You'll leave the college with a job in hand

44:19.752 --> 44:21.710
Above all give this serious thought

44:21.752 --> 44:23.794
Do you want to be ruled by a girl?

44:23.835 --> 44:25.460
Or revel in a boy's leadership?

44:29.210 --> 44:32.294
Hey! That isn't even my glass

44:32.335 --> 44:35.002
Some other chap has relished
a drink and gone, madcap!

44:35.044 --> 44:36.169
How dare you!

44:36.877 --> 44:38.544
1 'JD' please

44:56.919 --> 44:59.335
'3rd round of votes
have been counted'

44:59.585 --> 45:02.252
'We have started counting
for the 4th round'

45:05.377 --> 45:06.252
Sir...?

45:06.294 --> 45:07.502
'4th round, sir'

45:07.627 --> 45:09.419
Results are due any moment

45:10.127 --> 45:11.627
I'm scared, sir

45:16.085 --> 45:18.335
Are you Satyaraj acting
as Amavasai in 'Amaidhi Padai'?

45:18.377 --> 45:19.502
4th round it seems

45:19.544 --> 45:20.585
Pah!

45:20.752 --> 45:24.752
'Most awaiting election results
are going to be declared very soon'

45:28.627 --> 45:31.752
'Fourth and final election results
are going to be declared'

45:32.585 --> 45:35.294
Bhargav 2588 votes

45:35.377 --> 45:37.877
'Savitha 2648 votes'

45:37.960 --> 45:40.377
'Savitha won the election by 60 votes'

45:43.127 --> 45:44.585
[loud cheering]

45:57.419 --> 45:59.252
Congratulations, chairperson

45:59.460 --> 46:02.627
Sir, I think they have already
started creating a ruckus there

46:02.669 --> 46:04.085
Sir, what do we do now?

46:04.127 --> 46:06.877
Why do you still ask me?
She's the captain of your ship

46:06.919 --> 46:09.085
Chairman, tell us what to do?

46:10.585 --> 46:11.544
'Sir'

46:11.585 --> 46:16.002
To avoid all these unnecessary confusion
I'm thinking of talking to Bhargav directly

46:16.419 --> 46:17.460
Look at that!

46:17.710 --> 46:19.044
By all means go and talk

46:19.169 --> 46:20.419
But go alone

46:21.585 --> 46:22.669
Madam

46:22.794 --> 46:26.002
Don't dilly-dally, scratch your head,
crack your knuckles and keep looking back

46:26.044 --> 46:27.752
Don't dawdle and
do 'instalment' walk

46:27.794 --> 46:29.044
Forward march!

46:31.710 --> 46:34.669
Sir, will you give me your bracelet?

46:35.002 --> 46:35.919
Why?

46:35.960 --> 46:37.002
Please give, sir

46:37.044 --> 46:38.127
'Dude, play that song'

46:38.788 --> 46:43.497
"Look! We must lead a life like that bird
Without a care in the world"

46:43.529 --> 46:47.988
"We should go on a dancing spree
like the waves here in glee"

46:48.038 --> 46:52.455
"Under the same sky spacious
On the same land so precious"

46:52.504 --> 46:57.087
"Under the same sky endless
On our Motherland peerless"

46:57.252 --> 47:01.002
"Let's sing in unity our song
of what is our right all along"

47:01.044 --> 47:02.502
I want to talk to you

47:02.585 --> 47:05.877
If she comes offering a truce
I'll break the bones on her face

47:05.960 --> 47:08.252
[song from 'Aayirathil Oruvan']

47:09.585 --> 47:11.335
- Bro, tell me
- 'What happened?'

47:11.377 --> 47:12.752
Your son lost, bro

47:13.044 --> 47:13.919
What?

47:13.960 --> 47:15.669
Bhargav...er-

47:16.085 --> 47:17.794
I came to congratulate

47:18.044 --> 47:21.919
Winning by just 60 votes
is no big victory at all

47:22.544 --> 47:26.002
Er...is there any rule in college
there should be only 1 chairman?

47:26.085 --> 47:28.919
You take over day college
and I'll handle evening college

47:29.960 --> 47:31.377
Okay, bye

47:32.583 --> 47:33.585
Congrats

47:34.210 --> 47:36.210
I extended my hand
even on nomination day

47:36.252 --> 47:37.835
You didn't want to shake hands

47:40.710 --> 47:42.377
At least let it be truce now?

47:43.669 --> 47:45.919
I don't think it's safe
for her to go alone

47:45.960 --> 47:47.669
Shall I go and check, sir?

47:56.585 --> 47:57.835
'Let's shake hands'

47:59.002 --> 48:00.544
- Okay
- How ridiculous

48:00.585 --> 48:02.127
He has patched up happily

48:02.327 --> 48:04.077
'He is shaking hands
with that girl who won'

48:04.127 --> 48:05.127
'Let me talk to him'

48:05.169 --> 48:06.169
1 minute, bro

48:06.210 --> 48:07.210
'Bhargav brother'

48:08.377 --> 48:11.252
Dad, there's no problem
I spoke to that girl

48:11.294 --> 48:13.460
She even asked me to be
the chairman for Day college, pa

48:13.544 --> 48:16.627
'You got a sudden desire to
beg a post from her, huh?'

48:16.752 --> 48:19.710
It isn't what you think, pa
I'll come in person and explain

48:22.377 --> 48:24.669
- Bro
- 'Pack him home in our car now'

48:24.710 --> 48:25.752
Okay, bro

48:25.794 --> 48:27.530
'If he refuses to go, threaten him'

48:27.572 --> 48:30.364
- 'Rough up that female who defeated him'
- I'll handle it

48:31.419 --> 48:33.669
I'll explain to my dad
Please don't create a ruckus

48:33.710 --> 48:36.669
He has given me permission
to scar even your face, bro

48:36.710 --> 48:37.960
First get inside

48:38.252 --> 48:39.710
But please don't hurt that girl

48:39.752 --> 48:41.585
Sir, he wasn't nasty to me

48:41.627 --> 48:43.335
I shook hands and he said okay

48:43.919 --> 48:45.002
That's all

48:45.044 --> 48:46.460
Celebrations are done

48:46.835 --> 48:48.627
Hey! Catch

48:48.669 --> 48:49.710
Wear these IDS

48:49.752 --> 48:51.752
- Where's the booth?
- 1st floor, bro

48:51.835 --> 48:52.919
'Hurry up'

48:54.960 --> 48:56.752
Clear up all this mess
and then celebrate

48:56.794 --> 49:01.044
Sir, evening college students are
planning to burn down the booth

49:10.669 --> 49:12.377
- Who is he?
- Professor, bro

49:12.419 --> 49:14.169
- What, da?
- That wasn't a proper election

49:14.210 --> 49:17.002
- We demand re-election or re-counting
- Election is over, that's all

49:17.085 --> 49:19.044
- Burn down the booth
- Which department are you?

49:19.085 --> 49:20.835
- Come here
- Stop this idle talk

49:20.877 --> 49:23.002
I'll kill you
I'll break all your teeth!

49:23.044 --> 49:24.502
- Sri, quiet!
- 'Give that bottle'

49:24.544 --> 49:25.710
- Wait
- Sir...!

49:27.710 --> 49:29.919
- Sir, let go
- 'Shut up, all of you'

49:30.669 --> 49:31.835
I'm trying to make peace-

49:31.877 --> 49:33.544
Siiiiir
Move aside

49:33.585 --> 49:36.419
Evening college chairman candidate
Bhargav wants to talk to you, sir

49:36.460 --> 49:38.085
'My dad didn't listen to me'

49:38.127 --> 49:41.002
He has sent 50-60 Party riff-raffs
to bash up everyone in college

49:41.044 --> 49:44.460
'They have merged with the students
Ensure our college students are safe, sir'

49:49.252 --> 49:50.919
On the starboard!

49:50.960 --> 49:53.377
- 'Why are all of them spinning?
- What are they doing?'

49:53.419 --> 49:55.502
Now close your eyes and freeze

49:55.585 --> 49:57.585
'What is this?
Tell us, bro'

49:57.627 --> 49:59.169
'Sticking to the wall like glue?'

49:59.210 --> 50:00.210
Move forward

50:00.252 --> 50:01.794
'They are doing just the opposite'

50:01.835 --> 50:03.044
'Wait, don't go'

50:07.669 --> 50:10.085
Send all the girls home safe

50:10.248 --> 50:12.123
- Sir?
- Just do as I say

50:12.627 --> 50:14.544
Hey! Take all of them
through the back door

50:14.585 --> 50:16.085
Go...go...fast

50:16.127 --> 50:17.127
'Go now'

50:40.460 --> 50:41.794
SAVITHA, YOU GO!

50:42.710 --> 50:44.419
Hey! That's the girl

50:44.460 --> 50:45.502
'Grab her'

50:51.127 --> 50:52.127
Savitha

50:55.085 --> 50:56.419
Hey...hey!

51:01.794 --> 51:02.835
Hey!

51:06.223 --> 51:07.514
Are you okay?

51:12.960 --> 51:14.377
Go in...quick

51:18.210 --> 51:20.710
Sir, students are all out of control

51:26.210 --> 51:27.419
Let me go

51:27.460 --> 51:29.377
- Take your hands off
- Sir...sir

51:29.419 --> 51:30.794
TAKE YOUR HANDS OFF!

51:34.335 --> 51:37.044
How dare you manhandle girls!

51:57.460 --> 51:58.585
Master...!

52:20.794 --> 52:23.085
Nothing major, just a nail scratch

52:23.127 --> 52:26.085
Dai! Meeting is being held in the library

52:26.127 --> 52:27.460
Is everyone safe, da?

52:27.502 --> 52:28.752
'I have checked all the groups'

52:28.794 --> 52:29.794
They have texted me

52:29.835 --> 52:33.044
The entire riot has been recorded
in our college CCTV cameras

52:33.085 --> 52:34.585
Is he behaving like a professor?

52:34.627 --> 52:37.169
Excuse me, ma'am, you are
talking about damage of property

52:37.210 --> 52:39.794
Rowdies got together and
bashed up 4-5 of our girls

52:39.877 --> 52:41.835
What could all the teachers do?

52:41.877 --> 52:44.044
- No one came to stop them
- Stop it, Charu

52:44.169 --> 52:46.710
It isn't even 1 month
since you joined this college

52:46.752 --> 52:47.877
Just keep quiet

52:48.585 --> 52:51.210
What the hell are they discussing?

52:51.335 --> 52:52.377
I'll be back

52:52.919 --> 52:54.085
I'll talk to JD

52:54.127 --> 52:56.044
Then we will take a call

52:56.085 --> 52:59.169
If he intends coming back
we are resigning, sir

52:59.210 --> 53:01.585
'WTH is this meeting in aid of?'

53:01.669 --> 53:05.085
Sir, I have already given
a commitment I'll resign

53:05.127 --> 53:06.502
I'm just leaving this college

53:06.544 --> 53:08.210
JD, just wait in the car

53:08.252 --> 53:09.669
- 'I need to talk to you'
- Sir...?

53:09.710 --> 53:10.919
I said 'wait'

53:14.169 --> 53:15.335
'I understand'

53:15.377 --> 53:17.252
If they need to know your worth

53:18.002 --> 53:19.544
A gap is essential

53:21.252 --> 53:22.919
Your decision is correct

53:23.127 --> 53:25.085
You wanted a break for 3 months?

53:25.169 --> 53:26.502
I have okayed it

53:28.085 --> 53:29.210
When did I ask?

53:34.669 --> 53:36.127
Isn't this your signature?

53:38.460 --> 53:39.460
Sir

53:40.127 --> 53:41.419
Carbon copy, sir

53:41.460 --> 53:42.919
Oh! Come on, JD

53:43.835 --> 53:46.669
Haven't you opted for a break
of 3 months, intending to teach?

53:46.710 --> 53:48.960
Teach? In which college?

53:49.960 --> 53:51.002
College?

53:51.377 --> 53:53.544
As you have mentioned
Observation Home

53:54.377 --> 53:56.252
Sir, don't play the fool

53:56.294 --> 53:57.710
What will I do there?

53:57.794 --> 53:59.210
I didn't sign this

54:01.085 --> 54:03.544
Maybe after 6:00 p.m?

54:07.585 --> 54:09.210
After 6:00 p.m

54:09.502 --> 54:10.669
Good chance

54:10.960 --> 54:11.960
See

54:12.752 --> 54:15.585
JD, you're losing control on yourself

54:18.919 --> 54:22.669
If there's any issue in the election
didn't you agree to resign your job?

54:23.252 --> 54:25.419
That means you have
something on your mind

54:26.127 --> 54:27.794
Fine, sir, I'll go

54:28.335 --> 54:30.335
Think...I have many 'well' wishers here

54:30.377 --> 54:32.044
This must be their handiwork

54:32.627 --> 54:34.585
It's okay, I need a change too, I'll go

54:34.669 --> 54:38.210
'Inspector is waiting at your place
to explain the job you'll be undertaking'

54:40.252 --> 54:41.502
'That means'

54:42.544 --> 54:43.752
- Needhimani
- Bro?

54:43.835 --> 54:45.419
You didn't pass on any information?

54:45.460 --> 54:46.752
No, bro

54:48.752 --> 54:50.960
Then whatever lawyer sir
and I spoke in the union office

54:51.002 --> 54:53.960
- How did the police get to hear?
- That's what puzzles me, bro

54:56.127 --> 54:58.335
You know this music director Anirudh?

54:58.877 --> 55:01.044
He has composed a new film song

55:01.210 --> 55:02.752
Shall we listen?

55:06.085 --> 55:07.460
- Listen
- 'Bro'

55:07.835 --> 55:10.752
'Bhavani has fixed the date
You are his next target'

55:10.835 --> 55:13.252
'He has decided to kill you too
by framing it on those boys'

55:13.294 --> 55:14.877
What do you say, bigamist?

55:15.544 --> 55:18.044
At least is this your voice
or will you claim its mimicry?

55:18.127 --> 55:20.335
- Bro
- Did you call me, Bhavani?

55:22.002 --> 55:25.752
Make sure the boys are supplied
their regular dose of drinks and drugs

55:26.085 --> 55:28.585
Whether they get
3 square meals a day or not

55:29.502 --> 55:31.710
Booze and dope should flow steadily

55:31.752 --> 55:33.627
Okay, Bhavani
I'll see to it

55:35.377 --> 55:36.377
Where was I?

55:36.419 --> 55:39.252
You got me married and how
can you make my wife a widow?

55:39.919 --> 55:41.169
- Tell me, bro
- Wait

55:41.210 --> 55:44.002
I'm choking with emotion
hearing your sentimental speech

55:48.252 --> 55:49.710
Why are you jerking?

55:50.127 --> 55:53.627
I had tucked the knife in my waist
What if it pierces me in the wrong place?

55:54.169 --> 55:56.877
- Not that
- Suppose an enemy kills us

55:56.919 --> 55:59.669
Doesn't matter if they say
'that's how Bhavani died a noble death'

55:59.710 --> 56:03.169
If they say, 'he had tucked a knife
that stabbed him in a wrong spot'

56:03.210 --> 56:04.502
Does that sound good?

56:04.544 --> 56:06.085
- No
- No, right?

56:06.169 --> 56:07.252
Won't sound good

56:07.335 --> 56:09.210
- Lean back comfortably
- Don't, bro

56:09.252 --> 56:10.919
- Is that a show of respect?
- Yes, bro

56:10.960 --> 56:13.877
How is it over the phone
all this 'bro' kinship is missing?

56:13.919 --> 56:15.127
What is this?

56:15.627 --> 56:17.210
- Lean back
- No, bro

56:17.460 --> 56:19.585
Won't you comply with
your bro's death wish for you?

56:19.630 --> 56:21.671
Lean back...sit...sit...sit!

56:21.736 --> 56:22.903
LEAN BACK!

56:32.627 --> 56:33.919
Dai Gopal!

56:35.294 --> 56:36.794
- Hey
- 'Yes, bro'

